---

Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; slice into 1⁄4-inch-thick quarter-moons. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}. Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{1}.

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain and rinse under cold water for at least ~{30%seconds}; shake off any excess water.

In a #large bowl{}, combine drained cavatappi, cucumber, tomatoes, scallions, beans, @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, @creamy balsamic dressing{3%ounce}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, half the @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, 1/2 tsp @salt{1/2%tsp}, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}. Toss until well coated. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Refrigerate until ready to serve.

Place @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until softened, ~{15-20%seconds}. Stir in remaining garlic powder.

Halve @ciabatta bread{1} lengthwise and toast until golden. Spread with garlic butter.

Cut garlic toast on a diagonal into triangles.

Divide pasta salad between bowls. Serve with garlic toast on the side.

> Best of all, it's on the table in a speedy 20 minutes!